======================================================================
PART 2: Hamiltonian PATH fixed-point analysis
======================================================================

  No Hamiltonian path is fixed by σ: i ↦ i+1 mod p
  (Proof: σ(v₀,...,v_{p-1}) = (v₀+1,...,v_{p-1}+1) = (v₀,...,v_{p-1})
   iff v_i+1 = v_i for all i, which is impossible for distinct v_i)
  Therefore ALL orbits have size p, confirming THM-212. □

======================================================================
PART 3: The H(P_11) = 5×7×11×13×19 miracle
======================================================================

  H(P_11) = 95095 = 5 × 7 × 11 × 13 × 19
  Five CONSECUTIVE ODD primes!

  H(P_19) = 1172695746915
  Factorization: {3: 2, 5: 1, 7: 1, 11: 1, 19: 1, 23: 1, 774463: 1}

  H(P_11) = 95095
  Factorization: {5: 1, 7: 1, 11: 1, 13: 1, 19: 1}

  H(P_7) = 189
  Factorization: {3: 3, 7: 1}

  Which primes divide H(P_p)?
    P_3: H = 3 = 3
      Prime divisors: [3]
    P_7: H = 189 = 3^3×7
      Prime divisors: [3, 7]
    P_11: H = 95095 = 5×7×11×13×19
      Prime divisors: [5, 7, 11, 13, 19]
    P_19: H = 1172695746915 = 3^2×5×7×11×19×23×774463
      Prime divisors: [3, 5, 7, 11, 19, 23, 774463]

